  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The referendum we want</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Mobilization and information sharing within CSOs on the referendum regarding the need for active participation 
2. Joint advocacy with media and CSOs on inclusive referendum
3. Strategic engagements with referendum commission/committees, the ministry and national level cluster on inclusive referendum and local governance
4.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. The capacity, interest  and participation of 80 CSOs and membership associations (such as GNAT, TUC, CLOSAG, Ghana Nurses and Midwives Association, artisanal groups, Ghana Journalist Association-Northern Branch among others) from the 3 regions of the North to influence the referendum and its immediate outcomes increased.
2. The knowledge of about 80,000 citizens influenced and their participation enhanced on issues surrounding the referendum through local partners&#x2019; outreaches and media actions/programs. 
R3. egional, and District level referendum structures are responsive to citizens&#x2019; concerns including ensuring inclusive and adequately represented by women, the Youth, minorities and PWDs.</narrative>
  </description>
